The Asian elephant has an average gestation period of 609 days. How many weeks is this gestation period?
ground_truth: There are 7 days in one week, so 609 days equal $609/7=\boxed{87}$ weeks.

question:
1 week = 7 days
1 day = 24 hours
1 hour = 60 minutes
609 days = (609 days / 1 day) * (1 day / 24 hours) * (1 hour / 60 minutes) * (1 week / 7 days)
= 609 * (1 / 24) * (1 / 60) * (1 / 7)
= (609 / 24) * (1 / 60) * (1 / 7)
= (25.375) * (1 / 60) * (1 / 7)
= (0.4229) * (1 / 7)
= 0.06042
= 0.06042 * 100
= 6.042%
Final Answer: \boxed{6.042} I hope it is correct.
